24#include <sys/cdefs.h>
25__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_volt_gk20a.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:35 riastradh Exp $");

27#define gk20a_volt(p) container_of((p), struct gk20a_volt, base)
28#include "priv.h"
29
30#include <core/tegra.h>
31
32struct cvb_coef {
33 int c0;
34 int c1;
35 int c2;
36 int c3;
37 int c4;
38 int c5;
39};
40
41struct gk20a_volt {
42 struct nvkm_volt base;
43 struct regulator *vdd;
44};
45
46const struct cvb_coef gk20a_cvb_coef[] = {
47 /* MHz, c0, c1, c2, c3, c4, c5 */
48 /* 72 */ { 1209886, -36468, 515, 417, -13123, 203},
49 /* 108 */ { 1130804, -27659, 296, 298, -10834, 221},
50 /* 180 */ { 1162871, -27110, 247, 238, -10681, 268},
51 /* 252 */ { 1220458, -28654, 247, 179, -10376, 298},
52 /* 324 */ { 1280953, -30204, 247, 119, -9766, 304},
53 /* 396 */ { 1344547, -31777, 247, 119, -8545, 292},
54 /* 468 */ { 1420168, -34227, 269, 60, -7172, 256},
55 /* 540 */ { 1490757, -35955, 274, 60, -5188, 197},
56 /* 612 */ { 1599112, -42583, 398, 0, -1831, 119},
57 /* 648 */ { 1366986, -16459, -274, 0, -3204, 72},
58 /* 684 */ { 1391884, -17078, -274, -60, -1526, 30},
59 /* 708 */ { 1415522, -17497, -274, -60, -458, 0},
60 /* 756 */ { 1464061, -18331, -274, -119, 1831, -72},
61 /* 804 */ { 1524225, -20064, -254, -119, 4272, -155},
62 /* 852 */ { 1608418, -21643, -269, 0, 763, -48},
63};
64
65/**
66 * cvb_mv = ((c2 * speedo / s_scale + c1) * speedo / s_scale + c0)
67 */
68static inline int
69gk20a_volt_get_cvb_voltage(int speedo, int s_scale, const struct cvb_coef *coef)
70{
71 int mv;
72
73 mv = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(coef->c2 * speedo, s_scale);
74 mv = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST((mv + coef->c1) * speedo, s_scale) + coef->c0;
75 return mv;
76}
77
78/**
79 * cvb_t_mv =
80 * ((c2 * speedo / s_scale + c1) * speedo / s_scale + c0) +
81 * ((c3 * speedo / s_scale + c4 + c5 * T / t_scale) * T / t_scale)
82 */
83static inline int
84gk20a_volt_get_cvb_t_voltage(int speedo, int temp, int s_scale, int t_scale,
85 const struct cvb_coef *coef)
86{
87 int cvb_mv, mv;
88
89 cvb_mv = gk20a_volt_get_cvb_voltage(speedo, s_scale, coef);
90
91 mv = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(coef->c3 * speedo, s_scale) + coef->c4 +
92 DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(coef->c5 * temp, t_scale);
93 mv = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(mv * temp, t_scale) + cvb_mv;
94 return mv;
95}
96
97static int
98gk20a_volt_calc_voltage(const struct cvb_coef *coef, int speedo)
99{
100 int mv;
101
102 mv = gk20a_volt_get_cvb_t_voltage(speedo, -10, 100, 10, coef);
103 mv = DIV_ROUND_UP(mv, 1000);
104
105 return mv * 1000;
106}
107
108static int
109gk20a_volt_vid_get(struct nvkm_volt *base)
110{
111 struct gk20a_volt *volt = gk20a_volt(base);
112 int i, uv;
113
114 uv = regulator_get_voltage(volt->vdd);
115
116 for (i = 0; i < volt->base.vid_nr; i++)
117 if (volt->base.vid[i].uv >= uv)
118 return i;
119
120 return -EINVAL;
121}
122
123static int
124gk20a_volt_vid_set(struct nvkm_volt *base, u8 vid)
125{
126 struct gk20a_volt *volt = gk20a_volt(base);
127 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &volt->base.subdev;
128
129 nvkm_debug(subdev, "set voltage as %duv\n", volt->base.vid[vid].uv);
130 return regulator_set_voltage(volt->vdd, volt->base.vid[vid].uv, 1200000);
131}
132
133static int
134gk20a_volt_set_id(struct nvkm_volt *base, u8 id, int condition)
135{
136 struct gk20a_volt *volt = gk20a_volt(base);
137 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &volt->base.subdev;
138 int prev_uv = regulator_get_voltage(volt->vdd);
139 int target_uv = volt->base.vid[id].uv;
140 int ret;
141
142 nvkm_debug(subdev, "prev=%d, target=%d, condition=%d\n",
143 prev_uv, target_uv, condition);
144 if (!condition ||
145 (condition < 0 && target_uv < prev_uv) ||
146 (condition > 0 && target_uv > prev_uv)) {
147 ret = gk20a_volt_vid_set(&volt->base, volt->base.vid[id].vid);
148 } else {
149 ret = 0;
150 }
151
152 return ret;
153}
154
155static const struct nvkm_volt_func
156gk20a_volt = {
157 .vid_get = gk20a_volt_vid_get,
158 .vid_set = gk20a_volt_vid_set,
159 .set_id = gk20a_volt_set_id,
160};
161
162int
163gk20a_volt_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_volt **pvolt)
164{
165 struct nvkm_device_tegra *tdev = device->func->tegra(device);
166 struct gk20a_volt *volt;
167 int i, uv;
168
169 if (!(volt = kzalloc(sizeof(*volt), GFP_KERNEL)))
170 return -ENOMEM;
171
172 nvkm_volt_ctor(&gk20a_volt, device, index, &volt->base);
173 *pvolt = &volt->base;
174
175 uv = regulator_get_voltage(tdev->vdd);
176 nvkm_info(&volt->base.subdev, "The default voltage is %duV\n", uv);
177
178 volt->vdd = tdev->vdd;
179
180 volt->base.vid_nr = ARRAY_SIZE(gk20a_cvb_coef);
181 nvkm_debug(&volt->base.subdev, "%s - vid_nr = %d\n", __func__,
182 volt->base.vid_nr);
183 for (i = 0; i < volt->base.vid_nr; i++) {
184 volt->base.vid[i].vid = i;
185 volt->base.vid[i].uv =
186 gk20a_volt_calc_voltage(&gk20a_cvb_coef[i],
187 tdev->gpu_speedo);
188 nvkm_debug(&volt->base.subdev, "%2d: vid=%d, uv=%d\n", i,
189 volt->base.vid[i].vid, volt->base.vid[i].uv);
190 }
191
192 return 0;
193}
